35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 11:40:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> I got one of these today, and some folks told me it was for a quest for a weight reduction bag.<br><br>does anyone have any infomation? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utramddarkluxdeorum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tramddark Luxdeorum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 12:00:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> I forget the quest givers name, but its a man on the ground floor left side of the concilium universum in katta castellum, in the same room as a woman, give it to him for the pack's sketch, he'll give you the other details. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquasinomdeplume.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quasinom de Plume</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bullhonkie.com/ubb/admin5.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 12:16:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> *Copied from <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com">Allakhzam's</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->*<br><br>You say, 'Hail, Rallic Aristos' <br><br>Rallic Aristos says 'Well met Daias ! I am Rallic Aristos, Governor of trade and economy here in Katta Castellum. I know it sounds like a lot of parchment pushing and coin counting but maintaining good trade relations with the various Houses of Shadow Haven and the haggling Vah Shir of Shar Vahl is not as easy at it may sound. Then there is the issue of the [acrylia mines] in the Tenebrous Mountains. <br><br>You say, 'what acrylia mines?' <br><br>Rallic Aristos says 'The Tenebrous Mountains are rich with veins of the valuable acrylia ore. Unfortunately the mines were dug and controlled by a tribe of savage grimlings from the forests to the south. Negotiations have been attempted with the grimlings but to no avail. Several of the other governors and I have been developing a [plan] to take the mines or establish mines of our own. In either case the mines will have to be defended from attacks by the grimlings unless when placed in that predicament they finally resort to trade negotiations. <br><br>You say, 'what plan?' <br><br>Rallic Aristos says 'The full plans are not at my disposal but one of my concerns that may be instrumental in our success is the acquisition of grimling documents carried by a grimling courier who is seen frequently running from the forest to the mines. If one of the Validus Custodus attempts to obtain the runners pouch the grimlings will surely retaliate, if adventurers like yourselves obtained it however and quietly delivered it to me we may be able to move forward with our plans. <br><br>The grimling runner is found on the southern side of the zone. He drops a pack (LORE) which you turn into Rallic Aristos in Katta. <br><br>He gives you back a pattern. You then combine the Rallic Pattern (LORE), a shade silk thread (2 shadeling silks combined), a shade silk cord (3 shade silk threads combined), and a Perfect owlbear pelt (drops off higher level Owlbears) in a sewing kit to receive your Rallic Pack.<br><br>Starts in Katta Castellum. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udindolur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dindolur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 5:28:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> Stats on the pack is: 10 slot, 85% WR, wt 1.0 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskoobin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skoobin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://skoobin5881.homestead.com/files/v_anim.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 6:28:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> wow nice...gotta get me onna these. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 10:06:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> Anyone know what faction you need to do the quest and what tailoring skill is needed to do the combine?<br><br>Is the container no drop? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uliseutdubard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LiseutDuBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 10:28:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> The runners pack was no drop however the pattern is not.  The resulting back pack is lore but not no drop.<br><br>Liseut, lunar bard of 49 seasons <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiscandar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iscandar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 10:34:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> My tailoring skill is 65 (or there abouts, no higher than 69), and the pack was trivial for me.  Have made about 6 of them, have not failed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubuzweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>buzweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 2:34:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> Hail All,<br><br>I've done this quest several times now. The hardest part is getting the Perfect OwlBear Pelt. The Trivial level is very low, mine is 120 so hard to say what the min triv is.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uoriaas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oriaas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/01 3:11:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grimling runners pouch?</span><hr size=1> When you turn the runner's pouch in to Rallic he blabs some stuff, but one thing I caught was what he said to do with it. I don't tend to log stuff because it never fails...<br><br>/log and I end up playing for 20 hours and forgetting the log is on...then forget I logged something important so the log sits there...then /log again until like the 4th or 5th time when I finally remember I logged something and struggle to find what it was I logged to start with.<br><br>Anyhow he said something to the effect of combine the pattern and gives you a list of what else in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>any</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> large sewing kit or loom (sp?). So that leads me to believe its a never fail item. Next pouch I snag, I will pass the pattern off to a twink and try to combine with no tailoring skill and see what message I get.<br><br>***EDIT***<br>Bold didn't show up as well as I thought on the grey cell so I underlined the word any. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uoriaas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oriaas</A> at: 12/24/01 3:14:14 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3588.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3607.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3606.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3606.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3606.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3606.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3606.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Tra